00:13:54.550 --> 00:13:56.000
You can drop the act.

265
00:13:56.035 --> 00:13:57.234
The act?

266
00:13:57.270 --> 00:13:58.736
Hey. man. you got it backwards.

267
00:13:58.772 --> 00:14:00.138
I dropped my act.

268
00:14:00.173 --> 00:14:02.673
You guys could stand
to do the same thing.

269
00:14:02.708 --> 00:14:04.942
Hey. Elaine.

270
00:14:04.977 --> 00:14:08.128
You're looking dynamite tonight.

271
00:14:10.950 --> 00:14:13.551
Corny. but sincere.

272
00:14:15.238 --> 00:14:17.721
Gotcha.

273
00:14:19.893 --> 00:14:21.692
Come on. let's go. honey.

274
00:14:21.727 --> 00:14:24.295
Poor. Latka.

275
00:14:24.330 --> 00:14:25.546
What do you mean. Jim?

276
00:14:25.581 --> 00:14:30.134
Everybody's beating
time with his woman.

277
00:14:30.170 --> 00:14:32.570
First Bobby. and now that jerk.

278
00:14:48.455 --> 00:14:49.735
Latka!

279
00:14:51.124 --> 00:14:52.404
Latka!

280
00:14:55.795 --> 00:14:57.128
Latka!

281
00:14:58.715 --> 00:15:00.047
Latka!

282
00:15:04.687 --> 00:15:08.890
Hey. man. what is your problem?

283
00:15:13.730 --> 00:15:16.547
I don't like people playing
music in this garage.

284
00:15:16.582 --> 00:15:18.110
Well. I don't like
this authority trip

285
00:15:18.134 --> 00:15:19.645
that you're always
laying on me. man.

286
00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:22.920
Hey. you just
wasted Elvis Costello.

287
00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:26.524
Latka. you're getting
weirder every day.

288
00:15:26.559 --> 00:15:28.420
Now. I don't want
to have to fire you

289
00:15:28.444 --> 00:15:30.545
for this. because...

290
00:15:30.580 --> 00:15:34.065
I don't want to
have to fire you...

291
00:15:34.100 --> 00:15:37.484
I was hoping to fire
you just for no reason.

292
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:39.215
Look. you better wise up.

293
00:15:39.239 --> 00:15:41.722
Knock it off.

294
00:15:41.757 --> 00:15:44.359
And try wearing some
decent clothes to work.

295
00:15:44.394 --> 00:15:46.310
You look like a foreign banana.

296
00:15:52.285 --> 00:15:56.587
Well... time for my
sparkling water break.

297
00:15:56.622 --> 00:15:57.955
Anybody want some?

298
00:15:59.993 --> 00:16:01.870
He's not coming out of this.

299
00:16:01.894 --> 00:16:03.305
If anything. it's getting worse.

300
00:16:03.329 --> 00:16:04.829
It's been going
on for a week now.

301
00:16:04.864 --> 00:16:06.163
night and day.

302
00:16:06.198 --> 00:16:07.509
Maybe somebody
should talk to him.

303
00:16:07.533 --> 00:16:08.799
Hey. I tried.

304
00:16:08.834 --> 00:16:11.919
He just keeps telling
me I'm one dynamite lady.

305
00:16:11.954 --> 00:16:14.789
I keep telling him
that's beside the point.

306
00:16:16.726 --> 00:16:18.526
Get an answering service.

307
00:16:18.561 --> 00:16:19.860
Hello.

308
00:16:19.896 --> 00:16:21.061
Yeah. Vic's here.

309
00:16:21.096 --> 00:16:22.296
Hold on a second.

310
00:16:22.331 --> 00:16:25.049
Hey. Latka. it's Karen for you.

311
00:16:25.084 --> 00:16:27.268
I'm not here.

312
00:16:27.303 --> 00:16:30.504
Latka. it's the girl you're
crazy about. remember?

313
00:16:30.539 --> 00:16:34.992
Hey. I am out man. read my lips.

314
00:16:41.100 --> 00:16:43.367
Uh. yeah. no. he's not here.

315
00:16:43.403 --> 00:16:44.835
Yeah. okay. sure.

316
00:16:44.870 --> 00:16:47.471
I'll tell him you called. Bye.

317
00:16:50.943 --> 00:16:52.560
Latka. what's going on?

318
00:16:52.595 --> 00:16:54.590
It's over between her and me.

319
00:16:54.614 --> 00:16:56.392
You see. Karen
is the kind of chick

320
00:16:56.416 --> 00:16:57.815
who craves rejection

321
00:16:57.850 --> 00:16:59.678
and goes around
creating it for herself.

322
00:16:59.702 --> 00:17:03.020
So what's a boy to do?

323
00:17:06.208 --> 00:17:08.675
This is too much.

324
00:17:08.711 --> 00:17:11.244
Latka. we got to talk to you.

325
00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:12.663
Hey...

326
00:17:12.699 --> 00:17:15.165
you know I always have
time to talk to you. Elaine.

327
00:17:15.201 --> 00:17:17.735
You're one dynamite lady.

328
00:17:17.771 --> 00:17:19.570
Latka. shut up.

329
00:17:19.606 --> 00:17:22.072
Ooh-hoo. redheads.

330
00:17:23.075 --> 00:17:24.141
I'm glad you feel

331
00:17:24.176 --> 00:17:26.277
that you can be so
honest with me like that.

332
00:17:26.312 --> 00:17:28.752
Latka. come here
and sit down. okay?

333
00:17:36.088 --> 00:17:37.733
Hey. Latka. Latka. you're weird.

334
00:17:37.757 --> 00:17:39.172
Hey. we're all coming

335
00:17:39.208 --> 00:17:40.741
from a different direction.

336
00:17:40.777 --> 00:17:42.976
and sometimes it
doesn't get in synch.

337
00:17:43.012 --> 00:17:45.379
Sorry about that.
but you had it coming.

338
00:17:49.118 --> 00:17:51.046
Latka. can't you
see what's going on?

339
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:53.131
Can't you see what
you're doing to yourself?

340
00:17:53.155 --> 00:17:55.539
Yeah. I'm assimilating.

341
00:17:55.575 --> 00:17:57.924
Hey. Latka. why don't
you come off it. huh?

342
00:17:57.960 --> 00:18:00.278
Hey. if I have to
be a cute little guy

343
00:18:00.313 --> 00:18:01.912
who strikes out every time

344
00:18:01.948 --> 00:18:04.482
in order to be
Mr. Popularity around here.

345
00:18:04.517 --> 00:18:07.385
well then you can
just keep your trophy.

346
00:18:08.988 --> 00:18:10.455
Would you just stop it?

347
00:18:10.490 --> 00:18:11.689
Well. excuse me.

348
00:18:11.724 --> 00:18:14.692
I thought that I had
the right to evolve.

349
00:18:14.727 --> 00:18:17.728
but I'm sensing a
lot of hostility here.

350
00:18:17.764 --> 00:18:21.549
Fortunately. I got
my friend Alex.

351
00:18:25.054 --> 00:18:27.054
My man. Alex.

352
00:18:27.090 --> 00:18:29.890
With a heart as
big as his schnoz

353
00:18:29.925 --> 00:18:32.826
and a brain as
sharp as his profile.

354
00:18:32.861 --> 00:18:34.339
Yeah. well. I'm very flattered.

355
00:18:34.363 --> 00:18:35.507
Very flattered.

356
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:36.664
Hey. man. you understand

357
00:18:36.699 --> 00:18:37.998
what I'm talking
about. don't ya?

358
00:18:38.033 --> 00:18:39.366
Yes. I think I do.

359
00:18:39.401 --> 00:18:40.501
Yeah.

360
00:18:40.537 --> 00:18:42.486
God bless the people.

361
00:18:42.521 --> 00:18:44.188
Adios. kids.

362
00:18:44.224 --> 00:18:45.356
Hey. where you going?

363
00:18:45.391 --> 00:18:46.524
Hey. come on back.

364
00:18:46.559 --> 00:18:48.125
Hey. man. don't leave me.

365
00:18:48.160 --> 00:18:49.354
Come on. I tell ya. Latka.

366
00:18:49.378 --> 00:18:51.545
I've been going back
and forth about this thing.

367
00:18:51.580 --> 00:18:53.848
because I think maybe
you're justified in thinking

368
00:18:53.883 --> 00:18:56.016
that there was a
patronizing element

369
00:18:56.052 --> 00:18:58.585
in the way people used
to treat the old Latka.

370
00:18:58.621 --> 00:19:00.838
But the thing that keeps
coming through to me is

371
00:19:00.873 --> 00:19:02.139
I like that old Latka.

372
00:19:02.175 --> 00:19:04.842
and I don't like you.

373
00:19:10.866 --> 00:19:14.368
Ooh. hard to get
happy after that one.

374
00:19:33.206 --> 00:19:34.505
Hey. Alex.

375
00:19:34.541 --> 00:19:36.185
I think we've got some
head-butting to do.

376
00:19:36.209 --> 00:19:38.020
You dropped a real load
of guano on me today.

377
00:19:38.044 --> 00:19:39.688
and I think we should
get out our shovels

378
00:19:39.712 --> 00:19:41.078
and see if we can...

379
00:19:54.394 --> 00:19:55.837
Please. don't slam
the door on me again.

380
00:19:55.861 --> 00:19:57.373
because I don't
think I could take that.

381
00:19:57.397 --> 00:19:58.829
I really want to talk to you.

382
00:19:58.864 --> 00:20:01.064
What do you have to say
you haven't said already?

383
00:20:05.572 --> 00:20:07.538
I cry at night.

384
00:20:08.691 --> 00:20:10.803
Alex. please help me.
you've got to help me.

385
00:20:10.827 --> 00:20:12.020
I don't know what to do.

386
00:20:12.044 --> 00:20:13.371
I'm stuck inside of
here. I don't like this guy.

387
00:20:13.395 --> 00:20:14.539
I don't remember
how I got in. No. no. no.

388
00:20:14.563 --> 00:20:15.807
I'll help you. I'll help
you. I'll help you.

389
00:20:15.831 --> 00:20:17.665
Listen. just sit
down. Just sit down.

390
00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:19.077
I don't like the fast lane.

391
00:20:19.101 --> 00:20:21.168
Well. I understand that.

392
00:20:21.203 --> 00:20:22.770
Well. can't you just stop it?

393
00:20:22.805 --> 00:20:24.382
I mean. be the
guy you used to be.

394
00:20:24.406 --> 00:20:26.006
Talk like you used to talk.

395
00:20:26.041 --> 00:20:27.753
I don't remember
how I used to talk.

396
00:20:27.777 --> 00:20:29.260
You don't remember?

397
00:20:29.295 --> 00:20:30.694
Think.

398
00:20:30.729 --> 00:20:33.364
I... I remember I
was a cute little guy.

399
00:20:33.399 --> 00:20:35.699
I had some kind of an accent.

400
00:20:35.734 --> 00:20:37.218
But I've worked at it so hard

401
00:20:37.253 --> 00:20:38.919
I've been doing it for so long.

402
00:20:38.955 --> 00:20:41.521
I just don't remember
what I used to sound like.

403
00:20:41.557 --> 00:20:43.637
Well. not much different
than you do now.

404
00:20:44.793 --> 00:20:45.926
You remember?

405
00:20:45.962 --> 00:20:47.261
Latka Gravas.

406
00:20:47.296 --> 00:20:50.130
Latka Gravas.<i> Ibeda.</i>

407
00:20:51.817 --> 00:20:52.983
Yeah.

408
00:20:53.018 --> 00:20:57.755
Yeah. I do remember
"Latka Gravas.<i> Ibeda."</i>

409
00:20:57.790 --> 00:20:59.823
I'll try it.

410
00:20:59.858 --> 00:21:03.427
Okay. Latka Gravas.

411
00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:10.334
<i>Ibeda.</i>

412
00:21:11.404 --> 00:21:14.488
Oh. it's no use.
Alex. I can't cut it.

413
00:21:14.523 --> 00:21:16.173
I can't. I went too far.

414
00:21:16.208 --> 00:21:18.676
I don't remember
what I sounded like.

415
00:21:18.711 --> 00:21:21.746
I can't sound like him
anymore so this is it.

416
00:21:21.781 --> 00:21:24.381
From here on in. the
highway's full of honky-tonks

417
00:21:24.416 --> 00:21:27.384
and one-nighters and no
place to go when the bars close.

418
00:21:27.419 --> 00:21:28.719
No. no. no. no. no.

419
00:21:28.755 --> 00:21:29.965
No. it doesn't
have to be that way.

420
00:21:29.989 --> 00:21:31.783
Oh. come on. cadet.
stop the snowfall.

421
00:21:31.807 --> 00:21:33.340
I can take the truth.

422
00:21:33.376 --> 00:21:35.876
Latka. Latka. just calm down.

423
00:21:35.911 --> 00:21:37.878
Don't try so hard.

424
00:21:37.913 --> 00:21:40.047
I mean. just trust
that Latka's in there.

425
00:21:40.083 --> 00:21:41.532
that he'll come out.

426
00:21:41.567 --> 00:21:42.533
Just trust it and relax.

427
00:21:42.568 --> 00:21:43.634
No way. buddy boy.

428
00:21:43.670 --> 00:21:45.602
Shh. shh. shh. shh.

429
00:21:45.638 --> 00:21:47.866
Now. remember. Latka
was a kind of quiet guy.

430
00:21:47.890 --> 00:21:49.089
Trust me.

431
00:21:49.124 --> 00:21:51.759
Just be quiet. just relax. okay?

432
00:21:51.794 --> 00:21:52.976
Mm-hmm. Think.

433
00:21:53.011 --> 00:21:54.678
He's in there somewhere?

434
00:21:54.714 --> 00:21:55.994
Right.

435
00:21:58.818 --> 00:22:01.202
Come on. Latka.

436
00:22:01.237 --> 00:22:02.937
Come on out. Latka.

437
00:22:02.972 --> 00:22:05.956
I know you're in
there somewhere.

438
00:22:05.991 --> 00:22:08.242
Okay. okay. I'm sorry.

439
00:22:12.381 --> 00:22:13.581
All right.

440
00:22:34.504 --> 00:22:36.237
Latka.

441
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:37.316
Yes. yes. yes.

442
00:22:37.340 --> 00:22:38.340
Good. good. good.

443
00:22:39.242 --> 00:22:41.208
Right. right.
right. right. right.

444
00:22:41.244 --> 00:22:43.227
You got it.

445
00:22:43.262 --> 00:22:44.640
Alex? Yes. Latka.

446
00:22:44.664 --> 00:22:46.524
Thank you very
much. You're welcome.

447
00:22:46.548 --> 00:22:48.182
Oh. there's so much
I want to tell you

448
00:22:48.217 --> 00:22:50.200
that has happened to
me since I last saw you.

449
00:22:50.236 --> 00:22:51.913
Oh. great. I'd love
to hear it. Sit down.

450
00:22:51.937 --> 00:22:57.908
Okay. Well... Oh. yeah.

451
00:23:00.546 --> 00:23:02.913
Wasn't that silly?

452
00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:06.028
I remember that.

453
00:23:06.052 --> 00:23:07.229
Yeah?

454
00:23:07.253 --> 00:23:08.696
<i>Playboy.</i>

455
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:10.054
Oh. yeah.

456
00:23:10.089 --> 00:23:12.423
I'll get us a couple of
beers... I'm listening.

457
00:23:20.399 --> 00:23:22.577
Yeah. well. you know.
that was another time.

458
00:23:22.601 --> 00:23:26.070
Oh. well... don't like you.

459
00:23:26.105 --> 00:23:28.466
Well. I'm sorry about that.

460
00:23:28.490 --> 00:23:32.054
Guano. guano...
Yeah. well. yeah. here.

461
00:23:36.115 --> 00:23:38.582
Then... Thank you very much.

462
00:23:41.070 --> 00:23:43.048
So go ahead. tell me
more. tell me more.

463
00:23:43.072 --> 00:23:44.566
Well. that's it. Oh...

464
00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:47.057
Then here I am.
and here you are.

465
00:23:47.093 --> 00:23:49.104
Well. it's nice to
have you back. Latka.

466
00:23:49.128 --> 00:23:50.672
All right.

467
00:23:50.696 --> 00:23:52.396
No. no. I'm only fooling.

468
00:23:52.431 --> 00:23:54.464
Where is your sense of humor?

469
00:24:31.570 --> 00:24:33.131
Night. Mr. Walters.

